WorkItem.Description:
I got the "new rawr version" email, and reloaded the EJ rawr web page; the footer still says 4.3.4.0, not 4.3.5.0.  I tried restarting my browser (google chrome) and flushing the cache, but it still says 4.3.4.
 
Is it possible the new version hasn't hit EJ yet, even though the announcement went out?
 
The WPF downloadable version has the newer (4.3.5.0) version number, so its not just that someone didn't bump the in-app version number.

Comments.Message: It's loading 4.3.5 for me. Have you tried Shift+F5 to force refresh?

I did do shift-reload, as well as flushing the cache.

I just removed all the temp internet files, and that made chrome 'notice' the change.

You might want to examine the server caching policy that it sets on pages.
